A very attractive Jaeger Custom made Mauser in 6mm Lee Navy 6mm Lee Navy(6mm U.S.N. or .236 Navy) 

It has a Mannlicher stock made of very attractive Tiger Stripe Maple. Sorry, my photos don't do the stock justice. When I turned my flash on to try and bring out the grain of the wood the glare from the flash was worse.

The action is marked "Spandau 1916", a K98 Mauser action.

This rifle was my Grandfather's. He grew up in Philadephia near Jaeger's shop (in Jenkintown PA, a suburb of Philadelphia.)

At the time my Grandfather had this rifle made he considered this to be one of the best available varmint rounds, he handloaded rounds that he said were devastating on the local groundhog population. (the time was pre-WWII)

It has a peep sight installed and it was also drilled for a scope, the period scope mount is included.

Included with this rifle is the original "Ideal" handloading tool that he used and  ~115 pieces of period WRA brass.

This rifle is a great package that shows what a well funded youth would get as a varmint rifle pre-WWII.

title: For Sale:  Custom made tactical rifle slings
location: Garden of the Gods, Colorado Springs, Colorado
postcontent:
Custom made rifle slings

I have been making rifle slings for friends and myself for a while, and have decided to start selling them.  Each sling will be made to your specifications after you place your order.  If I have all the materials in stock, turnaround can be as short as a day unless I am out of town or work gets crazy.

To give an example of the type and quality of the slings I build, I will provide the below sample which I recently made for a friend.

This is a single point sling made of one inch genuine multi cam (licensed by Crye Precision, not a knockoff) tubular nylon webbing.  The main loop is adjustable from 30 to 78 inches using the main slider on the sling and the adjustment points on the two fastex type buckles.  The leg of the sling (the part that connects to your rifle) is adjustable from 7 to 14 inches.  The clip that attaches to the sling mount is an HK style steel clip, and is covered by the included 3" elastic hook cover.  All three parts of the sling come together at an anodized welded steel triangle.  All of the stitching is double bar-tacked using heavy duty synthetic upholstery thread on an industrial sewing machine.  Three elastic strap keepers and one elastic hook cover are included with this sling.  In total, this sling has 3 quick release points.

Based on the preferences of my coworkers and friends, this is one of the more popular sling designs, which is why I am using it as my flagship.

If you want this sling modified, I can do the following and more:
-Add or remove length to the loop
-Change connection hardware
-Add or remove adjustment points
-Add or remove quick release points
-Add a bungee internal to the tubular webbing
-Use different color webbing and hardware

As pictured and described, I am selling this sling at the introductory price of $40.  If a sling you purchase from me breaks through normal use, I will repair or replace it for one year from the date of purchase.

I prefer to do business face to face.  I live near Garden of the Gods, and I work on Ft. Carson.
